        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> lean pork mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!) to the pan and cook for 4-5 min, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go, until starting to brown and crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1686661354833-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1686661354833-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1686661354833-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1686661354833-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1686661354833-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>Marmite</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to a bowl with your<strong> chilli relish</strong>, <strong>peanut butter </strong>and <strong>soy sauce </strong>and mix until combined – this is your <strong>Marmite satay sauce</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> spinach</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
